                            <comment id="156386" author="adilger" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 20:52:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess that the &lt;tt&gt;cancel_lru_locks&lt;/tt&gt; call will not cancel locks that are actively being held.  It might be worthwhile to add &lt;tt&gt;sync; sleep 1; sync&lt;/tt&gt; before this call to ensure that the dirty pages are flushed before the locks are cancelled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="156374" author="green" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2016 18:16:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the latest failures are the same wrt the cause - background write (from &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/bd38a7d4-36e7-11e6-80b9-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/bd38a7d4-36e7-11e6-80b9-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;) :&lt;/p&gt;

